    static <E> XSet<E> X.asX​(Set<E> oldSet)  
    static <E> XSet<E> X.synchronize​(XSet<E> set)
    Ensures that the returned XSet instance based on the passed set is thread safe to use.
    This normally means wrapping the passed set in a SynchSet, making it effectively synchronized.
    If the passed set already is thread safe (indicated by the marker interface ThreadSafe), then the set itself is returned without further actions.
